## Next Steps: Deploy on Vercel

1. Go to **[vercel.com](https://vercel.com)** → New Project → Import `Swastik023/ldm-vercel`
2. Add the following **Environment Variables** in Project Settings:

| Variable | Value |
|---|---|
| `MONGODB_URI` | `mongodb+srv://admin:rootroot@cluster0.rokteln.mongodb.net/...` |
| `NEXTAUTH_SECRET` | `changeme_in_production` (use a strong random value in prod) |
| `NEXTAUTH_URL` | `https://your-app.vercel.app` ← **change after first deploy** |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME` | `dowzpb9zj` |
| `CLOUDINARY_API_KEY` | `176364421865824` |
| `CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET` | `RyVI6c8GN3QMN7Rkpx0gGoOx0Ow` |

3. Click **Deploy** — the build will succeed ✅

> [!IMPORTANT]
> After the first deploy, Vercel will give you a URL like `https://ldm-vercel.vercel.app`. Go back to Environment Variables and update `NEXTAUTH_URL` to that URL, then **Redeploy**.
